Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Teisamenos. Probably same as Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 184, 10, though he does not have the reversed nu.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1144)
